main event: An unidentified object was reported observed over Minneapolis, Minnesota on 30 November 1953 at approximately 6:06 PM.
interesting points: The object was described as round, white, and luminous, changing color from white to yellow to green., It was observed for about 20 minutes at an estimated altitude of 3000 to 4000 feet., The object appeared to be the size of a basketball held at arm's length., Two air force officers viewed the object., No sound was heard during the sighting.
